caption: Very affordable lunch menu + delicious. Can’t get any better
Great food. Great people working here. Stop reading this and get there.

I have been looking around for chow mein. This was one of the restaurants I found with chow mein on their menu, but that's not what I got. I think the stuff I got was probably chop suey or something along those lines. It was vegetables in a goopy sauce and no noodles at all. It tasted sort of ok, but it's really not what I wanted. I actually did double check before I ordered to make sure their menu (through doordash) mentioned "noodles" in the description. Probably not going to go back.

Quick service, covid friendly pick up, food has always been cooked properly. Been getting food from here for over 6 years as a dinner treat when I don't want to cook. Get a lot of food for the price, which is great to make several meals out of. Sorry no photos this time, food is already deliciously eaten.

Some places do wonderful things with a steamer - this is not one of those places.  I had steamed vegetables and chicken with a rice side in garlic sauce.  Let me tell you, that's -exactly- what you get.  Nothing is seasoned, the food is bland as you can possibly imagine.  The most prevalent taste is the tap water in which the food is steamed.  The vegetables are frozen bag vegetables, the chicken is completely totally unidentifiable as chicken, and I swear that's instant rice.  I would personally avoid this place like the plague.

REALLY this is the best place in this area. I like the portions they give. And you can't finish it all in one day, unless your champ. In which case you probably order extra sides when you go to a restaurant.
